    clinicalReasoningObj: "Trace the IgE-FcεRI-mast cell degranulation cascade to explain omalizumab's mechanism at the molecular level",
    questionType: "advanced",
    clinicalTopic: "immunology",
    pharmacologyFocus: "moa,receptor_activity,adverse_effects",
    bennerBreakdown: "Proficient asthma biologic management requires matching the patient's biomarker phenotype (IgE level, eosinophil count) to the appropriate biologic target — omalizumab for IgE-high allergic asthma, anti-IL-5 for eosinophilic, dupilumab for overlapping Type 2 inflammation."
