    examTip: "Naloxone dosing: Opioid overdose with respiratory depression: 0.4-2mg IV/IM/SC, repeat q2-3min (max ~10mg). Intranasal: 4mg (Narcan nasal spray). In OPIOID-DEPENDENT patients: start with 0.04-0.1mg IV (LOW dose) and titrate to respirations — goal is to restore breathing WITHOUT precipitating full withdrawal. Post-reversal monitoring: minimum 2 hours for short-acting opioids, 4-6 hours for long-acting. Nalmefene: longer-acting μ-antagonist (t½ ~11 hours) — may be preferred for long-acting opioid overdoses but higher risk of prolonged withdrawal.",
