    stem: "A 40-year-old female with opioid use disorder (OUD) on IV heroin is started on buprenorphine/naloxone (Suboxone) sublingual film for medication-assisted treatment (MAT). She must wait until moderate opioid withdrawal symptoms appear before induction. What is buprenorphine's unique receptor pharmacology, and why would premature induction precipitate withdrawal?",
